Name: ckanext-emailauth
Version: 0.1.0
Summary: Email authentication
Home-page: https://github.com/robinsax/ckanext-emailauth
Author: Robin Saxifrage
Author-email: robinsaxifrage@live.ca
License: AGPL
Description: #	What?
        
        A CKAN plugin that allows users to authenticate via email. The default authentication method is still supported.
        
        Tested on 2.7+.
        
        #	Why?
        
        So your CKAN users don't need to remember their passwords.
        
        #	How?
        
        Install like any other CKAN plugin. Check out the CKAN docs for a tutorial on how to do that.
        
        Unsurprisingly, requires an SMTP client (eg. postfix).
        
        Configuration includes:
        * `ckan.emailauth.login_key_expiry_hrs`, the number of hours a login email's link will stay valid. 
        	* Default 48.
        * `ckan.emailauth.login_key_size`, the number of bytes to use for the automatic login key.
        	* Default 20.
        * `ckan.emailauth.email_content`, a format string for the email. The formatted value is link HREF.
        	* Default authored for SAAB.
        * `ckan.emailauth.email_sender`, the name of the email sender. 
        	* Default 'login'.
        * `ckan.emailauth.email_subject`, the subject of the login email. 
        	* Default authored for SAAB.
         
        #	Who?
        
        Authored by Robin Saxifrage of [OpenGovGear](http://opengovgear.com) for [SAAB](http://saabnational.org).
